label.value: serotonin production involved in inflammatory response

value.value: The synthesis or release of serotonin following a stimulus as part of an inflammatory response, resulting in an increase in its intracellular or extracellular levels.
Any process leading to negative selection in B cells. Mechanisms of negative selection include anergy and deletion.

A series of reactions that takes place outside the cell occurring in response to tissue damage and initiated within blood plasma by the action of activated Factor XII (Hageman Factor) on prekallikrein to convert it to plasma kallikrein, and the subsequent reaction of plasma kallikrein with high molecular weight kininogen. The ultimate product of the plasma kallikrein-kinin cascade is bradykinin, an agent known to induce smooth muscle contraction, vasoconstriction, and increased vascular permeability.
Any process leading to negative selection of B cells in the bone marrow.
The series of events in which a stimulus from a tumor cell is received and converted into a molecular signal.
Any process leading to negative selection of B cells in the periphery.
Reactions triggered in response to the presence of a tumor cell that act to protect the cell or organism.

The non-specific expansion of B cell populations within a whole or part of an organism to reach to a total number of B cells which will then remain stable over time in the absence of an external stimulus.
The expansion of a B-1 B cell by cell division. Follows B cell activation.
The process in which a lymphoid progenitor cell becomes committed to becoming any type of T cell.

label.value: CD4-positive, CD25-positive, alpha-beta regulatory T cell differentiation

value.value: The process in which a precursor cell type acquires the specialized features of a CD4-positive, CD25-positive, alpha-beta regulatory T cell.

definition.value: Note that immunologists typically use the word 'development' to refer to cells of B or T cell lineages undergoing the process that GO describes as 'cell differentiation'.

label.value: CD4-positive, CD25-positive, alpha-beta regulatory T cell lineage commitment

value.value: The process in which a CD4-positive, alpha-beta T cell becomes committed to becoming a CD4-positive, CD25-positive, alpha-beta regulatory T cell.
The process in which a pro-T cell becomes committed to becoming an alpha-beta T cell.
The process in which a pro-T cell becomes committed to becoming an NK T cell.
The process in which a pro-T cell becomes committed to becoming a gamma-delta T cell.

label.value: leukocyte activation involved in immune response

value.value: A change in morphology and behavior of a leukocyte resulting from exposure to a specific antigen, mitogen, cytokine, cellular ligand, or soluble factor, leading to the initiation or perpetuation of an immune response.

label.value: cytokine production involved in immune response

value.value: The appearance of a cytokine due to biosynthesis or secretion following a cellular stimulus contributing to an immune response, resulting in an increase in its intracellular or extracellular levels.

value.value: Any process involved in the development or functioning of the immune system, an organismal system for calibrated responses to potential internal or invasive threats.

definition.value: Note that this term is a direct child of 'biological_process ; GO:0008150' because some immune system processes are types of cellular process (GO:0009987), whereas others are types of multicellular organism process (GO:0032501).

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate, or extent of the tissue kallikrein-kinin cascade.

label.value: immune response in brain or nervous system

value.value: An immune response taking place in the brain or nervous system.
An immune response taking place in the liver.
An immune response taking place in mucosal tissues, including those of the intestinal tract, nasal and upper respiratory tract, and genital tract.

label.value: immune response in gut-associated lymphoid tissue

value.value: Immune response taking place in the gut-associated lymphoid tissue (GALT). GALT includes Peyer's patches, appendix, and solitary lymph nodules.
Immune response taking place in the Peyer's patch, nodular lymphoid structures on the serosal surface of the small intestine.
Tolerance induction taking place in the Peyer's patches.

label.value: platelet activating factor production involved in inflammatory response

value.value: The synthesis or release of platelet activating factor following a stimulus as part of an inflammatory response, resulting in an increase in its intracellular or extracellular levels.

label.value: lysosomal enzyme production involved in inflammatory response

value.value: The synthesis or release of lysosomal enzymes following a stimulus as part of a inflammatory response, resulting in an increase in intracellular or extracellular levels.

label.value: tolerance induction in gut-associated lymphoid tissue

value.value: Tolerance induction taking place in the gut-associated lymphoid tissue (GALT).

label.value: immune response in nasopharyngeal-associated lymphoid tissue

value.value: An immune response taking place in the nasopharyngeal-associated lymphoid tissue (NALT). NALT includes the tonsils and adenoids.
The aggregation, arrangement and bonding together of a set of components to form an MHC protein complex.

label.value: MHC class I protein complex assembly

value.value: The aggregation, arrangement and bonding together of a set of components to form an MHC class I protein complex. Class I here refers to classical class I molecules.

label.value: MHC class Ib protein complex assembly

value.value: The aggregation, arrangement and bonding together of a set of components to form an MHC class Ib protein complex. Class Ib here refers to non-classical class I molecules.

value.value: Tolerance induction taking place in the mucosal-associated lymphoid tissue (MALT) mediated by T cells.

label.value: antigen sampling in mucosal-associated lymphoid tissue

value.value: The process of apical-to-basolateral delivery of soluble and particulate antigens to underlying mucosal-associated lymphoid tissue.

label.value: antigen sampling by dendritic cells in mucosal-associated lymphoid tissue

value.value: The process of antigen sampling carried out by dendritic cells in the mucosal-associated lymphoid tissue.
